llectual importance of the first imperial age, when the foundations were laid of versions of both Aristotelianism and Platonism which were bound to influence the whole history of European thought, from Late Antiquity onwards.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aPlatonists. 4aAristotelismus. 4aPierluigi Donini (Forscher). 4aPlatonismus. 4aPosthellenistische Philosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAristotelianism.  aPhilosophy, post-hellenistic.  aPierluigi Donini (scholar).  aPlatonism.1 aBonazzi, Mauro, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010z978311023355108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2010z9783110233575oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311021872540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311021873240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110218732423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110218732/original  a978-3-11-023355-1  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2010b2010  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  